Start with data wrangling

When data wrangling we will need a helper function for creating the quartiles for players. Additionally, it will be useful to exclude players that played less than 10 games or played less than 5 minutes a game. That is, we only want to include âqualifiedâ players.

Code 
# Returns quartile rank
quartile_rank <- function(x = 0:99) {
  # Set quartile
  quart_breaks <- c(
    -Inf,
    quantile(x,
      probs = c(.25, .5, .75),
      na.rm = TRUE
    ),
    Inf
  )
  cut(x = x, breaks = quart_breaks, labels = FALSE)
}
Solution
Code 
# Graphical data
nba_graph_dat <- nba_data %>% 
  # filter data only include players who played at least 10 games and averaged 5 mins a game
  filter(g >= 10, mp / g >= 5) %>% 
  # creating new columns that contain the quartile values in each statistic below for each qualifying player
  mutate(
    ts_quant = quartile_rank(ts_perc),
    trb_quant = quartile_rank(trb_perc),
    dbpm_quant = quartile_rank(dbpm),
    ast_quant = quartile_rank(ast_perc),
    usg_quant = quartile_rank(usg_perc)
  ) %>% 
  # select player name column and all quartile rank columns
  select(player, contains("_quant")) %>% 
  # transform data to long format with 3 total columns where the player column is unchanged, quartile column names are placed under "skill" column, and quartile column values are placed under "value" column
  pivot_longer(
    cols = -player, 
    names_to = "skill", 
    values_to = "value"
    ) %>% 
  # arrange by players in alphabetical order
  arrange(player)

Build the plot

Hints:

  • Image width is 8 in, height is 10 in â use code chunk yaml
  • center the image output â use code chunk yaml
  • shrink size down for display to 50% width â use code chunk yaml
  • All added text, except title, is done with annotate()
  • set axis.text to blank in theme
  • size 3 and 5 could be useful
Solution
Code 
# | label: skills-chart
# | fig-width: 8
# | fig-height: 10
# | fig-align: center
# | out-width: 50%

# identify player
player_name <- "LeBron James"

# plot data
plot_data <- nba_graph_dat %>% 
  filter(player == player_name)
  
# skills chart
ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = skill, y = value)) +
  geom_col(width = 1, fill = "#F28291") +
  geom_segment(
    x = 0.5:4.5,
    y = 0,
    xend = 0.5:4.5,
    yend = 4
  ) + 
  geom_hline(yintercept = 1:4, linetype = "dotted") +
  coord_polar() +
  scale_x_discrete(
    name = NULL,
    limits = c("ts_quant","usg_quant", "dbpm_quant","trb_quant","ast_quant"),
    expand = c(0,0)
  ) + 
  theme(
    axis.text = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks = element_blank(),
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 24, hjust = 0.5)
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    name = NULL,
    expand = c(0,0)
  ) +

  #sector label
  annotate(
    geom = "text",
    label= c("TRUE\nSHOOTING", "USAGE\nRATE", "DEFENSIVE\nBPM","REBOUND\nRATE", "ASSIST\nRATE"),
    x = 1:5,
    y = 6,
    size = 4
  ) +
   annotate(
    geom = "text",
    label= c("1st-25th", "25th-50th", "50th-75th","75th-99th"),
    x = 3,
    y = 0.7:3.7,
    size = 1.5
   ) +
  labs(
    title = str_c(player_name, "\n", "(2015)")
  ) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=14))
